Edition:
Quote:  The assassins, guided by three resident and professedly `friendly natives' of Poverty Bay, came to Captain Wilson's house ... <i>Ibid.</i> 25 The reason why they were allowed to escape the halter was this - in most cases the murderers were connected with friendly natives, and it was thought desirable not to offend those `friendlies', as they might prevent the settlement of the land question.
